# Frontend: Vite + React

## Project Context

NotebookLM is a chat-with-documents app. Keep the frontend clean, readable, and minimal.

## General

- **DRY**: Extract shared logic into hooks and utilities; avoid copy-paste.
- **No extra code**: Add only what the feature needs; remove unused imports and dead code.
- **Library components first**: Prefer components from a UI library (e.g. Radix, shadcn/ui) over custom implementations when they fit.

## Vite

- Use `import.meta.env.VITE_*` for env vars; keep proxy config in `vite.config.ts`.
- Use path aliases (`@/`) for cleaner imports if the project grows.
- Keep `index.html` at project root; entry point in `src/main.tsx`.

## React

- Use functional components and hooks only.
- Extract reusable logic into custom hooks (e.g. `useChat`, `useDocuments`).
- Keep components small and single-purpose; split when a component exceeds ~80 lines.
- Colocate component-specific styles (CSS modules or co-located `.css`).
- Use TypeScript for props and state; avoid `any`.

## Structure

```text
frontend/src/
  components/     # Reusable UI
  hooks/          # Custom hooks
  pages/          # Route-level components
  services/       # API calls
  types/          # Shared types
```
